{
  "text": "So far few studies have analyzed the coagulation and fibrinolytic systems during and after OPCAB in comparison with on-pump operations. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] A recent editorial [CITATION_4] hypothesized that OPCAB patients may have a higher risk of early graft failure because of the reduced activation of the fibrinolytic system associated with an enhanced activation of the inflammatory and coagulation systems.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "25366709",
